This paper deals with adapting neural machine translation to e-commerce domains, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves the use of language models and machine learning techniques, which are common in the sub-categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper involves data mining and information retrieval techniques, which are relevant to the sub-category of cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Finally, the paper involves image processing techniques for e-commerce domains, which is relevant to the sub-category of cs.CV (Computer Vision).
